reviews.text: I personally did not enjoy the food‚Äîit came across as bland and just not to my taste. On the positive side, the staff was friendly and the business itself was very clean, which I appreciated. They did have quite a few customers while I was there, so clearly many people do enjoy it, but unfortunately I was not one of them. Still, it might be worth trying for yourself as tastes can differ.

We ended up going here because our usual place was closed.  We were thoroughly impressed not only by the delicious food, but the customer service was top notch.
Very clean location.

Will definitely be returning to try more menu items.

The food was excellent. Been coming here for a few months now and they're always consistent. Definitely recommend their subs and their pizzas. The service though varies and it looks like they might be short staffed because today they had a very nice young boy working in the front but he looks like he didn't really wanna be there. I guess that's true for a lot of places now.

After living in NC for 3 years, the hunt for a great pizza place ended today. While my wife and I were out for a drive, we happened upon Rome Pizza. After looking at their menu, we decided to have the spinach pizza and a house salad. The salad arrived with crispy lettuce, tomato, mushroom, onion, green pepper and topped with shredded mozzarella cheese. We also had their house Italian dressing. So far, it was absolutely delicious. Then the pizza arrived. It was perfect!! The crust was crisp and fresh and nice and crisp under everything. This by far is the most delicious pizza we have ever had in NC. Rome pizza has new customers with us. Vahid was a very gracious host. Very easy and extremely friendly to talk to. After telling him about our pizza trials, he welcomed us back any time. We took a menu home and now we can‚Äôt wait to try all the other wonderful items on the menu. Thank you for the best pizza! Can‚Äôt wait to visit again!
Will Falzone

Ordered with the app for takeout and it went perfectly. The food was just being boxed up when I walked in. Everything was great!  I only wish Rome would use garlic bread sliced from a loaf versus the flat bread they use. For me, the flatbread is a little tough and chewy and we usually end up throwing most of it away. On this most recent order, I asked for it to be left off and they were happy to do so.
